00:34:04.647 --> 00:34:06.524
Don't be afraid to say it, brother.
That's right.


483
00:34:07.108 --> 00:34:07.942
A bitch.

484
00:34:08.025 --> 00:34:10.403
That's what Jesus Christ called you
in the Bible.


485
00:34:10.487 --> 00:34:12.696
[Barry] How come you're using
a King James Bible?


486
00:34:13.823 --> 00:34:16.576
-What?
-[chuckles] Why that edition?


487
00:34:16.659 --> 00:34:18.578
[stammers] I thought King James
was a white devil.


488
00:34:21.455 --> 00:34:23.874
Here's King James right here.
Take a good look.


489
00:34:25.417 --> 00:34:27.837
He looks like Billy Dee Williams
if you'd ask me.


490
00:34:29.046 --> 00:34:30.131
If you say so, brother.

491
00:34:33.426 --> 00:34:34.802
Now, you might ask...

492
00:34:34.885 --> 00:34:39.014
How did the Lost Tribes of Israel
become lost? Well, I'll tell you.


493
00:34:39.098 --> 00:34:41.767
[club music playing]

494
00:34:41.851 --> 00:34:43.102
[Saleem] How about her?

495
00:34:43.894 --> 00:34:45.688
-No way.
-Why not?


496
00:34:46.481 --> 00:34:48.899
She's trying way too hard.
Zero self-esteem.


497
00:34:48.983 --> 00:34:52.529
-[Saleem] So she'd sleep with me.
-[Charlotte] Um, probably?


498
00:34:53.028 --> 00:34:58.534
-So that's a yes, then.
-No. Big time no.


499
00:34:58.618 --> 00:35:01.871
I don't think you understand the nature
of this conversation, Charlotte.


500
00:35:01.954 --> 00:35:04.081
I don't really think I want to.

501
00:35:06.251 --> 00:35:08.836
Looks like your boyfriend's off
on Pluto again.


502
00:35:09.753 --> 00:35:13.090
Um... Ground Control to Barry.

503
00:35:13.757 --> 00:35:15.384
Oh, sorry. I was, um...

504
00:35:16.636 --> 00:35:17.720
-I was thinking...
-[Charlotte] No.


505
00:35:17.803 --> 00:35:19.013
-[Barry] Nah.
-[Charlotte chuckles]


506
00:35:19.889 --> 00:35:22.517
-Hey, Will.
-Hi, guys. What's up?


507
00:35:22.601 --> 00:35:25.645
Hey, Willy. What's this?
Buy one, get two free?


508
00:35:26.438 --> 00:35:29.064
-[chuckles]
-[Barry] You wanna join us?


509
00:35:29.148 --> 00:35:31.150
Uh... No, thanks.

510
00:35:31.233 --> 00:35:33.485
I think we're gonna check out
the band downstairs.


511
00:35:33.569 --> 00:35:37.031
-Okay. Well, um, I'll see you around.
-Yeah. See you, man.


512
00:35:38.866 --> 00:35:42.287
So, what are you guys doing
for Thanksgiving? Hmm?


513
00:35:42.369 --> 00:35:45.956
Anybody here dig,
uh, turkey tikka masala?


514
00:35:46.374 --> 00:35:48.460
I'm going to Connecticut.

515
00:35:49.835 --> 00:35:51.712
You guys are welcome to come with me.

516
00:35:51.795 --> 00:35:53.298
You can meet the clown
my sister's marrying.


517
00:35:53.381 --> 00:35:56.175
Well, I love clowns.
Let's go to Connecticut, Barry.


518
00:35:56.259 --> 00:35:59.011
I'm, um... I'm allergic to Connecticut.

519
00:35:59.094 --> 00:36:02.349
I break out into these,
um, gross white hives.


520
00:36:02.431 --> 00:36:04.725
Uh-
- Besides, I...

521
00:36:05.227 --> 00:36:07.270
I'm sure your, uh, family
would love you showing up


522
00:36:07.354 --> 00:36:08.854
with a Pakistani and a Black guy.

523
00:36:08.938 --> 00:36:10.482
Oh, well, you're not that black, Barry.

524
00:36:10.565 --> 00:36:12.149
-[scoffs]
-[Charlotte] No, seriously.


525
00:36:12.733 --> 00:36:13.943
They really wanna meet you.

526
00:36:14.026 --> 00:36:16.153
Uh, I wanna meet them too.

527
00:36:16.238 --> 00:36:19.949
But maybe we should do it
on a more neutral ground.


528
00:36:20.032 --> 00:36:22.034
Someplace with a lot of witnesses.

529
00:36:23.703 --> 00:36:25.871
I'm gonna go talk to that girl
with low self-esteem.


530
00:36:25.955 --> 00:36:28.375
Look, my parents are gonna love you.

531
00:36:28.458 --> 00:36:30.710
I'm sure some of their very best friends
are Black.


532
00:36:30.793 --> 00:36:32.379
They are, actually.

533
00:36:33.212 --> 00:36:35.547
-I was--
-I know what you were doing.


534
00:36:36.048 --> 00:36:40.135
The question is...
why you feel the need to do it.


535
00:36:41.971 --> 00:36:44.431
Look, I just really want
to spend Thanksgiving with you.


536
00:36:45.933 --> 00:36:48.311
Maybe we could do
it here, a day early.

537
00:36:49.688 --> 00:36:51.481
And then, I can go
to Connecticut by myself


538
00:36:51.564 --> 00:36:52.524
if you don't wanna come with me.

539
00:36:53.399 --> 00:36:55.818
[stammers] I'd like that.

540
00:36:57.987 --> 00:36:59.489
[Saleem] ...from the campus.

541
00:36:59.572 --> 00:37:03.867
-They're students. I'm not... really old.
-[both chuckle]


542
00:37:03.951 --> 00:37:06.912
[professor]
Now, here we have, if you'd like,


543
00:37:06.996 --> 00:37:11.626
a basic epistemological principle
that we must bear in mind.


544
00:37:11.710 --> 00:37:14.878
A genuine knowledge
involves cognitive union


545
00:37:14.962 --> 00:37:19.008
and overcoming
our estrangement or alienation.


546
00:37:19.091 --> 00:37:23.388
And this applies, I suppose,
to all spheres of our knowledge.


547
00:37:23.471 --> 00:37:26.516
I sometimes argue
that, to be a good scientist...


548
00:37:26.599 --> 00:37:30.687
[helicopter whirring]

549
00:37:36.817 --> 00:37:43.198
[siren wailing]

550
00:38:19.652 --> 00:38:20.653
[exhales deeply]

551
00:39:38.397 --> 00:39:42.151
So, I'm a little worried about Saleem
being in charge of Thanksgiving.


552
00:39:42.234 --> 00:39:43.569
I mean, can he even cook?

553
00:39:45.028 --> 00:39:48.115
Everything about that man is a mystery,
including these ingredients.


554
00:39:48.198 --> 00:39:52.244
Uh, yeah, what is "ghee"? [chuckles]

555
00:39:53.412 --> 00:39:55.164
And, um... [clicks tongue]

556
00:39:55.247 --> 00:39:57.958
you may have gotten out
of Thanksgiving with my family,


557
00:39:58.041 --> 00:40:00.712
but that means I'm gonna have
to take you to my sister's wedding.


558
00:40:00.794 --> 00:40:03.297
-[Barry] Hmm...
-And you're gonna have fun.


559
00:40:05.675 --> 00:40:07.342
You know I'm gonna cause a scene
at that wedding.


560
00:40:07.426 --> 00:40:08.470
-Oh, really?
-Mm.


561
00:40:08.553 --> 00:40:11.096
Once folks get a load
of my moves on the dance floor...


562
00:40:11.180 --> 00:40:12.222
Be a miracle. [chuckles]

563
00:40:15.642 --> 00:40:16.977
-[Ann] Aloha!-[Ann] Aloha!
-Mom?


564
00:40:18.813 --> 00:40:21.524
-Surprise!
-[Saleem] Surprise!


565
00:40:21.608 --> 00:40:23.025
You're supposed to be in Jakarta.

566
00:40:23.108 --> 00:40:26.069
I had a conference in LA.
Oh, my word. And here I am!


567
00:40:26.153 --> 00:40:28.030
-Here she is!
-My beauty.


568
00:40:28.989 --> 00:40:29.990
Uh...

569
00:40:30.073 --> 00:40:32.367
[stammering] Uh... Mom.

570
00:40:33.243 --> 00:40:36.079
-Uh... This is, uh, Charlotte.
-Charlotte.


571
00:40:36.163 --> 00:40:38.541
Hello. Such a pleasure to meet you, Mrs.--

572
00:40:38.625 --> 00:40:41.669
Ann. Just Ann, honey.
It's nice to meet you, too.


573
00:40:41.753 --> 00:40:44.631
[slow music playing on radio]

574
00:40:46.173 --> 00:40:48.634
-Charlotte, some peas, please.
-Mm-hm.


575
00:40:49.301 --> 00:40:51.345
Barry, honey, do you have a salad bowl?

576
00:40:59.979 --> 00:41:03.440
-Does this work?
-How about a knife?


577
00:41:09.279 --> 00:41:10.573
How about this?

578
00:41:10.657 --> 00:41:14.911
-Not exactly Julia Child, huh?
-Well, Saleem's sort of a child.


579
00:41:14.994 --> 00:41:17.580
Oh, yeah?
Well, you're sort of a poopy-head.


580
00:41:18.497 --> 00:41:21.208
Is the atmosphere around here
always so intellectually charged?


581
00:41:21.291 --> 00:41:23.753
-Oh, yeah.
-Well, you know, as a feminist,


582
00:41:23.836 --> 00:41:27.549
I would never endorse this sort
of retrograde patriarchal paradigm


583
00:41:27.632 --> 00:41:30.718
that would paint you as a sort
of domesticating, civilizing presence


584
00:41:30.802 --> 00:41:33.012
-in this household.
-Oh, no. Of course not.


585
00:41:33.095 --> 00:41:35.848
But if I did, I would say
that you have got your hands full


586
00:41:35.932 --> 00:41:36.891
with these two knuckleheads.

587
00:41:36.975 --> 00:41:39.142
-[Charlotte chuckles]
-Damn, Barry.


588
00:41:39.226 --> 00:41:41.311
Your mom can talk some shit.

589
00:41:41.395 --> 00:41:42.855
[chuckles]

590
00:41:42.939 --> 00:41:45.567
[Charlotte] So, do we get to hear
some embarrassing stories


591
00:41:45.649 --> 00:41:46.733
about Barry or what?

592
00:41:48.193 --> 00:41:50.529
I'm sorry to be dull,
but I don't really have any.


593
00:41:50.613 --> 00:41:52.949
He was so easy.
Even his birth was easy.


594
00:41:53.032 --> 00:41:56.368
I was 19 at that time,
so that wasn't the easiest, and...


595
00:41:57.244 --> 00:41:59.914
Neither was his dad,
but what can I say?

596
00:41:59.997 --> 00:42:01.248
He's my darling boy.

597
00:42:02.165 --> 00:42:04.251
[Charlotte]
What wasn't easy about his dad?


598
00:42:04.501 --> 00:42:06.169
Barry barely talks about him.

599
00:42:06.253 --> 00:42:10.424
All I know is that he's some kind
of high-up government official.


600
00:42:11.341 --> 00:42:12.426
I only met him once.

601
00:42:13.385 --> 00:42:15.722
He showed up in Hawaii
when I was ten and...


602
00:42:15.804 --> 00:42:17.347
tried to tell me
how to live my life.

603
00:42:18.140 --> 00:42:20.643
That's not true.
He was around when you were little.


604
00:42:22.269 --> 00:42:24.772
He's a lovely man. We just
weren't well-suited for each other.


605
00:42:24.856 --> 00:42:26.649
-Hmm.
-[Barry] Hmm.


606
00:42:26.733 --> 00:42:30.862
Mm, 'cause he had another family
in Kenya, Mom. He lied to you.


607
00:42:30.945 --> 00:42:34.156
It's a little more complicated than that.
But we don't have to talk about it.


608
00:42:34.239 --> 00:42:36.909
Okay. She always defends him.

609
00:42:36.992 --> 00:42:37.659
You know what?

610
00:42:38.660 --> 00:42:39.870
He gave me you.

611
00:42:43.290 --> 00:42:45.960
But Barry must've had
some terrible haircuts, at least.


612
00:42:46.044 --> 00:42:48.587
This is true. I
used to cut his hair.

613
00:42:48.671 --> 00:42:52.050
Mm. That's something
no white woman should do.


614
00:42:54.636 --> 00:42:55.845
Probably not.

615
00:43:01.183 --> 00:43:03.685
Your mom is awesome.

616
00:43:05.021 --> 00:43:07.732
Yeah, she's, uh... something, all right.

617
00:43:09.942 --> 00:43:11.986
No, seriously...

618
00:43:12.069 --> 00:43:16.114
How many girls from Kansas end up working
at the Ford Foundation in Indonesia?


619
00:43:17.075 --> 00:43:20.243
Well...
first, you marry an Indonesian guy.


620
00:43:20.327 --> 00:43:24.831
Then you... move to Indonesia
and, uh, realize you need a job.


621
00:43:27.752 --> 00:43:29.087
That's not fair.

622
00:43:31.296 --> 00:43:33.966
Yeah. No... no, it's not.

623
00:43:40.097 --> 00:43:42.057
What are you gonna do with her tomorrow?

624
00:43:42.725 --> 00:43:45.435
Most of the rest of the world
is having Thanksgiving.


625
00:43:47.979 --> 00:43:49.314
Yeah, well...

626
00:43:49.899 --> 00:43:51.818
I'm sure she'll have some ideas.

627
00:43:59.033 --> 00:44:02.704
[film projector rattling]

628
00:44:03.705 --> 00:44:07.917
[percussion music playing]

629
00:44:27.729 --> 00:44:32.357
[guitar music playing]

630
00:44:32.441 --> 00:44:34.067
[speaking Portuguese]

631
00:44:46.873 --> 00:44:49.708
[siren wailing]

632
00:44:52.211 --> 00:44:54.005
Is something wrong, honey?

633
00:44:55.422 --> 00:44:57.008
No. I'm just thinking about the movie.

634
00:44:58.092 --> 00:44:59.468
About you and the movie.

635
00:45:02.220 --> 00:45:05.348
And what was it you loved so much?
When you first saw it, I mean.


636
00:45:07.434 --> 00:45:08.685
It was beautiful.

637
00:45:10.395 --> 00:45:11.897
It was so exotic.

638
00:45:13.149 --> 00:45:14.942
I'd never seen anything like it.

639
00:45:16.903 --> 00:45:17.904
Like Dad?

640
00:45:26.411 --> 00:45:29.664
-Your dad hasn't written, has he?
-Why?


641
00:45:33.335 --> 00:45:35.880
Well, he's fallen on hard times,
I'm afraid.


642
00:45:37.380 --> 00:45:38.340
What happened?

643
00:45:39.591 --> 00:45:42.636
You know, it's all second-hand,
but he's not working, and...


644
00:45:43.012 --> 00:45:45.056
When he's not working,
he has a tendency to drink.


645
00:45:48.226 --> 00:45:49.852
He invited me to visit.

646
00:45:51.603 --> 00:45:53.940
That is fantastic.

647
00:45:54.023 --> 00:45:56.025
Oh, honey,
there's a whole part of you there


648
00:45:56.107 --> 00:45:57.692
just waiting to be discovered.

649
00:45:58.401 --> 00:45:59.821
This isn't Roots, Mom.

650
00:45:59.904 --> 00:46:02.531
[busker] ♪ This land was made
For you and me ♪


651
00:46:02.614 --> 00:46:04.158
Okay, now, this takes me back.

652
00:46:04.242 --> 00:46:05.827
[busker] ♪ This land is your land ♪

653
00:46:05.910 --> 00:46:09.831
[Ann and busker] ♪ This land is my land,
From California... ♪


654
00:46:09.914 --> 00:46:12.499
-Right on, brother.
-[busker] ♪ To the New York island ♪


655
00:46:12.582 --> 00:46:14.293
That is so corny, Mom.

656
00:46:14.376 --> 00:46:18.672
♪ From the redwood forests
To the Gulf Stream waters ♪


657
00:46:18.755 --> 00:46:21.591
♪ This land was made
for you and me ♪

658
00:46:23.135 --> 00:46:24.803
How are you, Barry?

659
00:46:25.887 --> 00:46:27.013
How are you, really?

660
00:46:29.308 --> 00:46:30.684
-Honestly?
-Yeah.


661
00:46:32.811 --> 00:46:34.146
I don't know. [scoffs]

662
00:46:35.522 --> 00:46:37.440
Well, sometimes, 
I feel like I wanna...

663
00:46:38.233 --> 00:46:39.943
breathe in everything
New York has to offer.


664
00:46:40.986 --> 00:46:42.487
Just make it all mine.

665
00:46:43.613 --> 00:46:48.870
Just... And other times,
it all seems like one... big distraction.


666
00:46:50.495 --> 00:46:53.373
People seem like distractions. [scoffs]

667
00:46:54.374 --> 00:46:55.959
I feel like I could... just...

668
00:46:57.377 --> 00:46:58.963
stop talking and...

669
00:46:59.754 --> 00:47:00.882
I don't know, just...

670
00:47:02.591 --> 00:47:03.216
disappear.

671
00:47:05.176 --> 00:47:08.471
And become a monk.
And, uh, read and write, and...


672
00:47:09.014 --> 00:47:09.931
think for a year.

673
00:47:11.142 --> 00:47:12.351
Don't do that.

674
00:47:14.102 --> 00:47:16.688
You know, every time
I open my mouth in class, it's like...


675
00:47:17.856 --> 00:47:20.692
I'm supposed to speak
on behalf of all Black people.


676
00:47:22.444 --> 00:47:24.363
Meanwhile, I, uh...

677
00:47:25.530 --> 00:47:27.241
I quit going
to Black Student Union meetings


678
00:47:27.324 --> 00:47:31.620
because [stammers]
I didn't feel like I belong there either.


679
00:47:38.543 --> 00:47:40.212
[sighs]

680
00:47:46.010 --> 00:47:48.012
The world is a big place, honey.

681
00:47:49.347 --> 00:47:50.889
You'll find your way.

682
00:48:01.233 --> 00:48:02.318
-[PJ] Oh.
-[man 1] Ooh.


683
00:48:02.401 --> 00:48:05.445
[PJ] Oh... Oh...

684
00:48:06.446 --> 00:48:07.530
Come on, now. Oh!

685
00:48:08.531 --> 00:48:09.532
Oh...

686
00:48:09.616 --> 00:48:12.827
Go up, big man! Go up.

687
00:48:14.996 --> 00:48:17.791
Come on, and let's see. Let's see.

688
00:48:20.877 --> 00:48:22.129
Uh-oh.

689
00:48:22.213 --> 00:48:23.588
-Oh!
-That's a good-ass turn.


690
00:48:23.672 --> 00:48:27.509
Ladies and gentlemen,
young Ralph Ellison in the house tonight!


691
00:48:27.592 --> 00:48:29.719
I know you can't see him.

692
00:48:29.803 --> 00:48:31.846
Uncover your eyes, he already invisible.

693
00:48:35.267 --> 00:48:36.601
-[PJ] Oh!
-[man 2] Oh!


694
00:48:36.685 --> 00:48:37.769
[PJ] Oh!

695
00:48:38.937 --> 00:48:39.771
[PJ] Oh, my goodness.

696
00:48:39.854 --> 00:48:41.189
[man 3]
That's what I'm talkin' about, baby!


697
00:48:41.773 --> 00:48:44.150
[PJ] That's the reason
they call him the Invisible Man.


698
00:48:44.235 --> 00:48:46.278
[Saleem urinating]

699
00:48:46.362 --> 00:48:47.989
[Saleem sighs] Okay.

700
00:48:48.947 --> 00:48:51.700
[sighs] Let me give you
some real-deal Saleem advice.


701
00:48:51.783 --> 00:48:54.203
You want to impress her parents?

702
00:48:54.285 --> 00:48:58.039
Order for her. Don't ask her
what she wants, just, um...


703
00:48:58.124 --> 00:49:02.585
[imitating Barry] I'll have the lobster
and a magnum of your finest champagne.


704
00:49:02.669 --> 00:49:07.466
And the lady will have, uh... a salad,
with a glass of water... with lemon.


705
00:49:07.549 --> 00:49:12.388
[in normal voice] Or... how about
whatever they ask you,


706
00:49:12.470 --> 00:49:16.141
you start every answer
with, um, "Shit, motherfucker."


707
00:49:16.641 --> 00:49:22.522
So... "Barry, New York must be
quite the change from Hawaii."


708
00:49:23.482 --> 00:49:26.193
"Shit, motherfucker, it sure is!"

709
00:49:26.776 --> 00:49:28.236
[Saleem chuckling]

710
00:49:28.319 --> 00:49:33.825
"[stammers] Have you started to think
about the summer yet, Barry?"


711
00:49:33.908 --> 00:49:39.581
"Shit, motherfucker. I'm considering
taking an internship at a law firm."


712
00:49:39.664 --> 00:49:41.458
These are, uh... 
They're all great ideas.

713
00:49:43.377 --> 00:49:45.379
-Damn it.
-Here, here. Let me.


714
00:49:45.463 --> 00:49:46.422
Yeah.

715
00:49:46.505 --> 00:49:50.134
You know, there's a lot about me
that you don't know, my brother.


716
00:49:50.216 --> 00:49:54.471
For example, I used to work at a bank
for almost two years.


717
00:49:55.472 --> 00:49:56.765
And I never, ever--

718
00:49:56.848 --> 00:49:57.974
