1186
01:27:51.454 --> 01:27:52.747
I'm kind of an uptight guy.

1187
01:27:57.084 --> 01:27:59.503
Great! Now all the ladies.

1188
01:28:16.480 --> 01:28:17.689
[photographer] Ready?

1189
01:28:20.483 --> 01:28:23.903
[Ephraim] It's the second time this week.
The second.


1190
01:28:24.404 --> 01:28:28.032
Listen, you have to take it easy.
You know they're not like back home.


1191
01:28:30.785 --> 01:28:31.577
Hello, sir.

1192
01:28:32.953 --> 01:28:37.709
-Can I get you something?
-No, no. I'm just, um, I'm killing time.


1193
01:28:52.766 --> 01:28:53.974
How you guys doing today?

1194
01:28:55.309 --> 01:28:56.268
Fine, sir.

1195
01:28:59.564 --> 01:29:01.817
-My name's Barry.
-Fred.


1196
01:29:02.859 --> 01:29:04.026
Ephraim.

1197
01:29:11.200 --> 01:29:14.036
-Where you guys from?
-We are Ugandan.


1198
01:29:15.204 --> 01:29:16.664
I thought so.

1199
01:29:17.915 --> 01:29:20.292
My, uh... father is from Kenya.

1200
01:29:20.376 --> 01:29:22.086
Ah! [chuckles]

1201
01:29:23.379 --> 01:29:24.631
Here you go.

1202
01:29:24.713 --> 01:29:25.840
Yeah. He...

1203
01:29:27.091 --> 01:29:28.384
He died recently.

1204
01:29:29.553 --> 01:29:32.221
My condolences to you and to your family.

1205
01:29:32.304 --> 01:29:33.432
Mine as well.

1206
01:29:35.057 --> 01:29:36.267
Yeah, thanks.

1207
01:29:38.562 --> 01:29:40.020
Yeah. It was today, actually.

1208
01:29:40.730 --> 01:29:41.565
[glass clinks]

1209
01:29:41.647 --> 01:29:42.273
I, uh...

1210
01:29:43.775 --> 01:29:48.070
I got a phone call this morning
from, uh, from an aunt I never met.


1211
01:29:57.621 --> 01:30:01.792
Actually, you know what?
[stammers] I will have a drink.


1212
01:30:04.921 --> 01:30:08.633
-What do you got back there?
-It's a full bar, sir.


1213
01:30:10.801 --> 01:30:11.677
I'll have a...

1214
01:30:12.804 --> 01:30:14.138
I'll have a vodka.

1215
01:30:38.746 --> 01:30:39.330
Cheers.

1216
01:30:50.299 --> 01:30:52.636
-How you doing?
-[chuckles]


1217
01:31:02.394 --> 01:31:04.856
-Yeah, this is my boyfriend, Barry.
-[man] Oh, hi.


1218
01:31:04.940 --> 01:31:06.566
-Barry.
-Good to meet you.


1219
01:31:06.650 --> 01:31:09.360
-Barry, this is Donna.
-Barry.


1220
01:31:09.443 --> 01:31:11.362
-Ted.
-Barry.


1221
01:31:11.445 --> 01:31:13.030
-And Emily.
-Pleasure.


1222
01:31:13.782 --> 01:31:17.243
-Oh, and this is my cousin, Melissa.
-Barry.


1223
01:31:18.202 --> 01:31:19.370
Hey.

1224
01:31:20.287 --> 01:31:23.499
Barry, there's someone
I'm dying to introduce you to.


1225
01:31:23.583 --> 01:31:25.334
-Just when I thought I'd met everyone.
-Hmm.


1226
01:31:40.432 --> 01:31:43.770
Barry, meet James and Grace Lee.

1227
01:31:43.853 --> 01:31:47.356
Two of the most brilliant,
committed writers and activists


1228
01:31:47.439 --> 01:31:49.943
-I have ever had the pleasure to know.
-Well, I'm honored to meet you.


1229
01:31:50.735 --> 01:31:54.739
Grace Lee tried to convince Malcolm X
to run for Senate in '64.


1230
01:31:54.823 --> 01:31:57.199
-It almost worked, too.
-[Barry] Wow.


1231
01:31:57.867 --> 01:32:00.787
I thought you might want to meet them.
Especially because of your parents.


1232
01:32:05.584 --> 01:32:06.710
[James] Have a seat, Barry.

1233
01:32:10.005 --> 01:32:11.213
Are your parents in the movement?

1234
01:32:11.297 --> 01:32:13.299
Uh, no. Not really.

1235
01:32:13.841 --> 01:32:17.469
They're, uh, different races.
I'm guessing that's what Kathy meant.


1236
01:32:18.470 --> 01:32:20.472
Ah, I see.

1237
01:32:21.515 --> 01:32:26.562
[stammers] My mom's from Kansas,
and my dad's from Kenya.


1238
01:32:28.815 --> 01:32:30.609
I've only met him once, though.

1239
01:32:31.818 --> 01:32:34.236
I grew up in Jakarta and Honolulu,

1240
01:32:34.320 --> 01:32:38.825
and spent a little time in California,
then, well, I ended up here.


1241
01:32:40.117 --> 01:32:41.368
That's some kinda gumbo.

1242
01:32:41.452 --> 01:32:43.788
[James and Grace Lee chuckle]

1243
01:32:44.831 --> 01:32:46.248
You know what that makes you,
young brother?


1244
01:32:47.291 --> 01:32:49.794
No, sir. [stammers] I don't.

1245
01:32:49.877 --> 01:32:52.004
I really, really don't.

1246
01:32:53.339 --> 01:32:57.176
It makes you American.
And you don't ever have to choose.


1247
01:33:03.265 --> 01:33:08.145
You know, I see you both
sitting here together, in love.


1248
01:33:08.270 --> 01:33:09.146
[chuckles]

1249
01:33:09.229 --> 01:33:11.231
-Yes, sir.
-And full of wisdom.


1250
01:33:11.732 --> 01:33:13.609
And I can't help but think that...

1251
01:33:14.318 --> 01:33:16.362
the two of you must have been
through all kinds of hell together.


1252
01:33:16.445 --> 01:33:20.616
Doing what you've done.
And looking how you look.


1253
01:33:20.700 --> 01:33:23.494
You take the baton
from the ones who've come before,


1254
01:33:23.577 --> 01:33:25.829
and you carry it
as far as you can.

1255
01:33:26.288 --> 01:33:27.665
And then you hand it off.

1256
01:33:28.999 --> 01:33:31.502
That's life. A beautiful struggle.

1257
01:33:33.420 --> 01:33:35.339
[Nina Simone's "I Will Be Released"
playing]


1258
01:33:54.274 --> 01:33:55.317
Hey.

1259
01:33:58.154 --> 01:33:59.363
Dance with me.

1260
01:36:57.708 --> 01:36:58.792
[Barry] "Dear Dad,

1261
01:37:00.128 --> 01:37:02.922
I am sorry it has taken me so long
to write you back.


1262
01:37:04.423 --> 01:37:07.010
I have thought of you
and your invitation to visit every day.


1263
01:37:07.969 --> 01:37:10.804
Sometimes I feel
that there's a part of me I do not know,


1264
01:37:12.723 --> 01:37:14.309
and when I am feeling optimistic,

1265
01:37:14.391 --> 01:37:16.978
I find myself believing that you hold
the answers I am looking for.


1266
01:37:19.146 --> 01:37:21.899
My journey so far has not been
as dramatic as yours,


1267
01:37:22.316 --> 01:37:25.569
but I'd like to think I can imagine
what you felt when you arrived in Hawaii.


1268
01:37:26.321 --> 01:37:28.697
Perhaps even what you felt
when you met Mom.


1269
01:37:30.616 --> 01:37:34.453
I suppose I have spent these last months
in New York trying to find my way.


1270
01:37:34.828 --> 01:37:36.830
Maybe that is all any of us do.

1271
01:37:38.498 --> 01:37:40.709
I look forward to discussing
these things with you, Dad.


1272
01:37:42.002 --> 01:37:44.046
It is high time we
got to know each other.

1273
01:37:45.881 --> 01:37:48.675
Love, Barack."

1274
01:38:59.496 --> 01:39:00.372
Hey.

1275
01:39:02.416 --> 01:39:03.125
You wanna play Horse?

1276
01:39:03.625 --> 01:39:05.794
-Sure.
-You can shoot first.


1277
01:39:09.298 --> 01:39:10.757
Oh, okay.

1278
01:39:12.592 --> 01:39:14.344
Woo! Nice one.

1279
01:39:24.021 --> 01:39:24.771
I got an H.

1280
01:39:27.400 --> 01:39:29.485
-Right here.
-Okay. [laughs]


1281
01:39:33.113 --> 01:39:36.366
Pretty good. Good. Guess I'm up.

1282
01:39:40.454 --> 01:39:41.496
Where you from?

1283
01:39:42.206 --> 01:39:46.918
-Riverside. How 'bout you?
-I'm from a lot of places.


1284
01:39:47.002 --> 01:39:49.546
But I... I live here now.

1285
01:39:52.133 --> 01:39:54.760
[T.L. Barrett and the Youth
for Christ Choir "Nobody Knows" playing]